text: Nasal flu vaccines being rolled out at the same time as strep A infections have risen means there is a link.
Nasal flu vaccines given to children contain strep A.
Nasal flu vaccines are causing the increase in strep A infections and deaths in young children.
The new nasal flu vaccine is linked to strep A cases.
The live flu vaccine has been found to cause strep A.
A study published in 2014 showed a connection between children’s nasal flu vaccines and strep A infections.
They’re using the same vaccine for strep A, Covid-19 and scarlet fever.
A study published in 2014 children’s nasal flu vaccines can cause strep A infections.
Something has been added to the flu vaccine nasal spray causing children to get very sick or die.
The nasal flu vaccine given to children contains streptococcal bacteria and aluminium, and is linked to the outbreak of deaths from strep A.
The swine flu vaccine used in the U.S. contains squalene, a dangerous adjuvant.
